Not every Kashmiri DEJHOR needs to be grand to make a statement.

Our Micro Mini DEJHORS are a quiet revolution—crafted in silver and sometimes gold-plated, they bring the sacred geometry of the hexagon (a nod to the traditional shutkone) into a size and style that fits today’s rhythm.

From the Turquoise drops to the Om and Shiv Shakti engravings, from soft pinks to the playful conch shell form—these pieces carry the soul of the original while staying light, wearable, and full of charm.

They’re easy to put on, light enough for daily wear, and rooted in centuries of symbolism.

Think of them as a gentle daily ritual—something your grandmother would bless, and your daughter would love.

Here’s what’s available right now:
	1.	Micro-mini Ruby Pink DEJHOR – warm, glowing, and full of softness.
	2.	Micro-mini Turquoise DEJHOR – vibrant, cool-toned, with a playful edge.
	3.	Micro-mini Shiv Shakti DEJHOR – etched with an Om on one side, and the Shiv Shakti star on the other.
	4.	Micro-mini Plain DEJHOR – minimal, strong, and elegant.
	5.	Micro-mini Shell DEJHOR – playful and charming .

DM to order, ask, or explore what feels most like yours.

Sun, pool, and a splash of turquoise .
This Turquoise Mini Dejhor is all elegance—with just the right pop of fun for summer. One side of the Mini dejhor bears the Shiv Shakti star, the other an Om, with three delicate turquoise drops dancing below. The Ath  or chain has turquoise interspersed with pearls.The Dejhors are perfect  whether or not you have the conch piercing.

Styled with a pearl necklace and layered with my favourite Hangul + honeybee charms on a chain.
Loving how the colours of my dress drift into the turquoise and the pool behind.
DM for a closer look or to make the jewellery yours. 
#ratikakauldejhors #ratikakauljewellery #custommadejewelry #madetoorderjewelry #kashmiripanditheritage #kashmirbrides #turquoisejewelry

Micro-Mini Dejhors—heritage in its most delicate form.
Strung on our signature Ruby Arts chains, these are not just inspired pieces—they are authentic Dejhors, scaled down to be worn every day, layered or solo.

We’ve paired them here with the Intrika coral necklace—a standout from our Intrika collection, crafted with large, beautifully set studs, adorned with corals and pearls. Each detail speaks of intricacy, tradition, and quiet opulence.

Available in pure gold or silver with gold plating, to suit your metal of choice.

DM us for prices or to customise your own set.
Because even the smallest pieces carry centuries of meaning.

Introducing the Micro Mini Dejhor - Pink 

A delicate fusion of tradition and modernity, this piece features the Shiv Shakti Star adorned with a radiant pink stone at its center—the Bindu, symbolizing the origin and union of all existence. Lightweight and effortlessly wearable, it’s a charming accessory that carries profound symbolism.

Perfect for daily wear or special occasions, this piece invites you to embrace its beauty and significance. Crafted in setting silver should not be wet.

💌 Please DM us to make this meaningful piece yours.

Stay tuned for our upcoming post showcasing the entire collection. Don’t miss out!

Turning up the sparkle 
You’ve loved the Micro Mini Dejhor for its delicate size, easy wear, and timeless charm—so I thought, why not give it a little glow-up?
This is. the diamond edition  Micro Mini Sparkle Dejhor 💎
Still dainty, still rooted in tradition, now lit up with a touch of glimmer—set in 22kt gold and available in both natural and lab-grown diamonds.

In this reel, I’m also wearing something very close to my heart—my Hangul studs and pendant, crafted in the form of the endangered Kashmiri stag that also forms my brand’s logo.
It’s a powerful symbol of heritage, resilience, and wild grace—now brought to life in a rich, diamond-studded version.
Customers can ask for these pieces too—both the earrings and the pendant.

Whether you’re layering the Dejhor for a wedding or adding the Hangul pendant to your everyday ritual, these pieces are full of meaning—and just the right amount of sparkle.

DM me for prices (both lab-grown and natural diamond options available). I’d love to hear from you. 💫

This is a Kashmiri Dejhor from my Shivshakti series.
The Mini Shivshakti Dejhor — small in scale, but complete in spirit.

 I’m showing you how it looks on two different chain lengths — first on a 4 cm chain, then on a longer 16 cm chain.
It changes how the piece sits, how it moves… how it.
this one is made with all three elements — the Ath (chain), The Dejhor (pendant), and the Athor (the star-shaped drop), and Ath are held together with a stud in the longer option where at the shorter option has needle hook clasp. A full set — just in a more delicate and unique silhouette.

Crafted in 22kt gold, and also available in silver with gold plating, for those who love a lighter, more everyday version.

If you’d like to see this piece up close, or understand the scale and details better, just DM me.
I’m always happy to share more — this work is deeply personal to me, and I love helping you find the piece that feels right for you.

There was a time when even I hesitated to wear the Dejhore.
Not because I didn’t value the tradition — but because I hadn’t yet found a version that felt practical, versatile, and suited my personal style.

I began designing jewellery 20 years ago and worked on the Dejhors to make them more wearable.
Like the  SYMMETRIKA DEJHOR — minimal, geometric, and striking in its simplicity. Available in both gold and silver with gold plating. And yes, you can wear it even without a piercing.
Lighter, easier to wear, can be styled to pair beautifully with both Indian and Western clothing — and more accessible in terms of price.

Now I find myself wearing them more than ever.

Please DM me if you’d like a closer look at or more details  Of the Symmetrika dejhor and Vintage chiffon Saree— I’d love to show you this piece up close.
The saree is a semi chiffon with a summary print and is edges and is edges with lace giving is very elegant vintage look that I personally love .
